data.enText: next to or at the side of sth

data.chText: 一辆警车在我们旁边停了下来。
data.enText: A police car pulled up alongside us.
together with or at the same time as sth/sb

data.chText: 现代城市生活方式盛行的同时，传统信念仍然大行其道。
data.enText: Traditional beliefs still flourish alongside a modern urban lifestyle.

data.chText: 尼克赶上了我，并排骑车前进。
data.enText: Nick caught up with me and rode alongside.

value.def: If one thing is alongside another thing, the first thing is next to the second.

example.ex: He crossed the street and walked alongside Central Park...
example.tran: 他穿过街道，沿着中央公园走。

example.ex: Much of the industry was located alongside rivers.
He waited several minutes for a car to pull up alongside.
example.tran: 他等了几分钟，直到一辆汽车靠边停下。

value.tran: 在…旁边；沿着…的边；与…并排靠拢

value.def: If you work alongside other people, you all work together in the same place.

example.ex: He had worked alongside Frank and Mark and they had become friends...
example.tran: 他与弗兰克和马克一起工作过，并且成了朋友。

example.ex: Men aged 60 are fighting alongside young boys.
example.tran: 年届六十的男人们和少年小伙们并肩作战。

value.def: If one thing exists or develops alongside another, the two things exist or develop together at the same time.

example.ex: Her self-confidence will develop alongside her technique...
example.tran: 随着她的技术不断提高，她会愈发自信。

example.ex: Alongside the Job Creation Programme they launched a Work Experience Programme.
example.tran: 在开展创造就业项目的同时，他们还启动了工作经历项目。
